"{\"uid\": \"centralwesterndaily.com.au-story-8721410-truck-driver-airlifted-after-crash-on-olympic-highway\", \"text\": \"Your digital subscription includes access to content from all our websites in your region.\\r Access unlimited content and the digital versions of our print editions - Today's Paper.  An investigation has been launched into the circumstances of aCentral Westhighway crash on Tuesday.  Loginor signup to continue reading  Paramedics from NSW Ambulance Service were called to the Olympic Highway near Crowther - About 40km north of Young - at around 2.30pm on August 6.  Once at the scene, they discovered a truck had crashed into a tree.  The driver, a 40-year-old man, was trapped before being freed by Fire and Rescue NSW. By the time paramedics arrived, the man had been freed from the truck.  A spokesman for NSW Ambulance Service described the incident as a \\\"single patient motor vehicle crash.\\\"  Paramedics assisted the 40-year-old who was then airlifted to Canberra Hospital.  NSW Police were also called to the scene of the crash.  A spokesman confirmed that an investigation into the circumstances surrounding the crashhad been launched.  Daily  Today's top stories curated by our news team. Also includes evening update.  Weekdays  Grab a quick bite of today's latest news from around the region and the nation.  Weekdays  Catch up on the news of the day and unwind with great reading for your evening.  Weekly  Get the editor's insights: what's happening & why it matters.  Weekly  Going out or staying in? Find out what's on.  Twice weekly  Stay in the know on news that matters to you with twice weekly newsletters from The Senior.  Weekly  Love footy? We have got all the action covered.  Weekly  The latest news, results & expert analysis.  Weekly  Every Saturday and Tuesday, explore destinations deals, tips & travel writing to transport you around the globe.  Weekdays  Sharp. Close to the ground. Digging deep. Your weekday morning newsletter on nationa